/diffgram/labels/user-request","name":"user-request","color":"FB5237","default":false,"description":""}],"state":"open","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2022-04-27T08:14:33Z","updated_at":"2022-04-27T14:05:05Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"NONE","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"# Use-Case\r\n\r\nWhen uploading custom model annotations to the platform, the raw polygons can consist of many (N>150) points and do not need to be 100% correct. \r\n\r\nIn the current setup, to correct invalid polygons I can either:\r\n- remove invalid points (Double-Clicking) or\r\n- adjust invalid points (Drag&Drop) or\r\n- delete the whole invalid polygon and draw a new one (e.g. using the Turbo Mode)\r\n\r\n\r\n# Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nIt would be great to have a brush/erase tool that allows to quickly fix invalid polygons. This way, we can use the full potential of the pre-annotations and do not have to adjust the raw polygons point-by-point. \r\n","closed_by":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/diffgram/diffgram/issues/832/reactions","total_count":2,"+1":2,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/diffgram/diffgram/issues/832/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}